We can also embed a structure within a structure. For example, associated with
our human-being structure we may wish to include the date of his or her birth. We can do this by writing:
typedef struct { int month;
int day;
int year;
} date;
typedef struct human—being { char name[10];
int age;
float salary;
date dob;
