Although strstr seems ideally suited to pattern matching, there are two reasons why we may want to develop our own pattern matching function:
The function strstr is new to ANSI C. Therefore, it may not be available with the compiler we are using.
(1)
There are several different methods for implementing a pattern matching function.
The easiest but least efficient method sequentially examines each character of the
string until it finds the pattern or it reaches the end of the string. (We explore this
approach in the Exercises.) If pat is not in string, this method has a computing
(2)

