\\textbf{Program 4.28:} Insertion into a doubly linked circular list

Deletion from a doubly linked list is equally easy. The function \\texttt{ddelete} (Program 4.29) deletes the node \\texttt{deleted} from the list pointed to by \\texttt{node}. To accomplish this deletion, we only need to change the link fields of the nodes that precede (\\texttt{deleted->llink->rlink}) and follow (\\texttt{deleted->rlink->llink}) the node we want to delete. Figure 4.26 shows the deletion in a doubly linked list with a single node.

